Author: Nexus-Digital-Automations <founder1@nexusdigitalautomations.com>
Date:   Tue May 5 21:51:57 2026 -0500

    Hash repo-index settings into the cache filename
    
    Cache key was previously the tree SHA alone. Settings that affect the
    rendered prefix bytes (repo_index_repomix_extra_args, chunk_size_tokens,
    chunk_overlap_tokens, embedding_model) weren't part of the key, so
    retuning any of them while staying on the same git tree would silently
    serve the old prefix bytes back from disk under a key DeepSeek thinks
    is fresh — full prefix-cache miss masquerading as a hit.
    
    Cache key is now f"{tree_sha}-{settings_suffix}" where settings_suffix
    is the first 8 hex chars of SHA-256 over the four fields. Filename
    becomes repo-<sha>-<suffix>.{txt,npy,json}. Old files become orphans
    on first run after the change and are pruned by the existing keep=3
    LRU.
    
    Counterpart helpers: _cache_key, _settings_cache_suffix in index.py.
    LoadedIndex.tree_hash now stores the combined key (it's the on-disk
    filename component); the existing test_repo_index_ac5_disk_artifacts_written
    test consumes it as such and stays green.
    
    Tests: 37/37 pass, ruff clean.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

